.TH ZEDIT 1 "2026-02-21" "zedit 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zedit \- modern console text editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zedit
.RI [ file ]
.br
.B zedit
.B \-\-help
.br
.B zedit
.B \-\-version
.br
.B zedit
.B \-\-ext
.RI { list | install | remove | info }
.br
.B zedit
.B \-\-import
.I file.vsix
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Zedit
is a modern console text editor written in pure Rust
with zero external dependencies. It features UTF\-8 native text handling,
modern desktop\-style keybindings (Ctrl+C/V/X/S/Z), syntax highlighting
via TextMate grammars, diff\-based rendering, multi\-cursor editing,
split panes, an integrated terminal, LSP client, git gutter, diff view,
minimap, and a plugin system. Part of the Z ecosystem (Zenith, Zymbol).
.PP
If
.I file
is given, it is opened for editing. Otherwise the previous session is
restored (if one exists), or a new empty buffer is created.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-ext " " { list | install | remove | info }
Manage native extensions installed in
.IR ~/.config/zedit/extensions/ .
.B list
shows all installed extensions.
.B install
.I <name>
installs an extension by name.
.B remove
.I <name>
uninstalls it.
.B info
.I <name>
shows its metadata.
.TP
.BR \-\-import " " \fIfile.vsix\fR
Import a VS Code extension package (.vsix) and install its grammar and theme
assets into the user configuration directory. Only grammar and theme files are
extracted; JavaScript code is ignored.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS File
.TP
.B Ctrl+S
Save file. If the buffer has no file name, prompts for one.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+S
Save As \(em prompts for a new file name.
.TP
.B Ctrl+O
Open file \(em prompts for a file path.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Q
Quit. If there are unsaved changes, press again to confirm.
.TP
.B Ctrl+N
Open a new empty buffer.
.TP
.B Ctrl+W
Close the current buffer (confirms if unsaved).
.TP
.B Ctrl+Page Down
Switch to the next buffer.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Page Up
Switch to the previous buffer.
.SS Edit
.TP
.B Ctrl+Z
Undo.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Y
Redo.
.TP
.B Ctrl+C
Copy selection (or current line if no selection). Line\-mode paste inserts above.
.TP
.B Ctrl+X
Cut selection (or current line if no selection).
.TP
.B Ctrl+V
Paste from clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+D
Duplicate current line.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+K
Delete current line.
.TP
.B Tab
Indent current line or selected lines.
.TP
.B Shift+Tab
Unindent current line or selected lines.
.TP
.B Ctrl+/
Toggle line comment (language\-aware).
.TP
.B Enter
Insert newline with auto\-indent.
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Move cursor up/down/left/right.
.TP
.B Home / End
Move to start/end of line.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Home / Ctrl+End
Move to start/end of file.
.TP
.B Page Up / Page Down
Scroll one page up/down.
.TP
.B Ctrl+G
Go to line number \(em prompts for a line number.
.SS Search
.TP
.B Ctrl+F
Find (incremental search, highlights all matches). Press
.B Ctrl+R
inside the search prompt to toggle regular expression mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl+H
Find and replace \(em prompts for search and replacement strings.
.TP
.B F3 / Shift+F3
Jump to next/previous search match.
.SS Selection
.TP
.B Shift+Arrow keys
Extend selection character by character or line by line.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+Left / Ctrl+Shift+Right
Extend selection word by word.
.TP
.B Ctrl+A
Select all.
.TP
.B Ctrl+L
Select current line.
.SS Multi\-Cursor
.TP
.B Ctrl+D
Add cursor at the next occurrence of the current selection (or select word
under cursor). Repeat to add more cursors. All cursors edit simultaneously.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+L
Select all occurrences of the current selection at once.
.TP
.B Alt+Click
Add a cursor at the clicked position.
.TP
.B Escape
Collapse all cursors to a single primary cursor.
.SS Panes
.TP
.B Ctrl+Backslash
Split the active pane horizontally (side\-by\-side).
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+Backslash
Split the active pane vertically (top/bottom).
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+W
Close the active pane.
.TP
.B Alt+Left / Alt+Right / Alt+Up / Alt+Down
Move focus to the adjacent pane in that direction.
.TP
.B Alt+Shift+Left / Alt+Shift+Right
Resize the active pane horizontally.
.TP
.B Alt+Shift+Up / Alt+Shift+Down
Resize the active pane vertically.
.SS View
.TP
.B F1
Toggle the in\-editor help overlay.
.TP
.B Alt+Z
Toggle soft word wrap.
.TP
.B Ctrl+B
Toggle the file tree sidebar.
.TP
.B Ctrl+P
Open the command palette (fuzzy\-searchable list of all editor actions and
plugin commands).
.TP
.B Alt+M
Toggle the minimap (braille code overview on the right edge of the pane).
.SS Terminal
.TP
.B Ctrl+T
Toggle the integrated terminal panel (persistent PTY).
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+T
Open a new terminal tab.
.TP
.B Shift+Page Up / Shift+Page Down
Scroll the terminal scrollback history.
.SS LSP (Language Server Protocol)
.TP
.B Ctrl+Space
Request LSP completions. A floating menu appears; use
.B Up/Down
to navigate,
.B Tab
or
.B Enter
to insert,
.B Escape
to dismiss.
.TP
.B Alt+K
Show hover documentation for the symbol under the cursor. Any key dismisses.
.TP
.B F12
Go to the definition of the symbol under the cursor.
If the definition is in another file, that file is opened in the active pane.
.PP
LSP diagnostics (errors and warnings) are shown with colored underlines in the
text and counted in the status bar. The language server is configured in
.IR ~/.config/zedit/config.json .
.SS Diff View
.TP
.B F7
Open a side\-by\-side diff of the current buffer versus its HEAD version in git.
.TP
.B F8
Jump to the next changed hunk.
.TP
.B Shift+F8
Jump to the previous changed hunk.
.TP
.B Up / Down / Page Up / Page Down
Scroll the diff view.
.TP
.B Escape
Close the diff view.
.SS Task Runner
.TP
.B F5
Run the default task for the current file's language (e.g.
.B zenith run
for Zenith,
.B cargo run
for Rust). Output is displayed in the integrated terminal.
.TP
.B Ctrl+F5
Build the project (e.g.
.B cargo build
for Rust).
.TP
.B Shift+F5
Run tests (e.g.
.B cargo test
for Rust).
.TP
.B Alt+F5
Stop the currently running task.
.SS Problem Panel
.TP
.B F6
Toggle the problem panel \(em a bottom overlay that aggregates errors and
warnings parsed from build output (Rust/Cargo, GCC, Clang, Python traceback,
and generic patterns). Use
.B Up
/
.B Down
to navigate the list and
.B Enter
to jump to the corresponding file and line.
.SS REPL Integration
.TP
.B Alt+Enter
Send the current selection (or the current line if nothing is selected) to the
language REPL running in the integrated terminal. Supported languages: Zenith
.RB ( zenith\ \-\-repl )
and Zymbol
.RB ( zymbol\ \-\-repl ).
A REPL session is started automatically if one is not already running.
.SS Mouse
.TP
.B Click
Position cursor.
.TP
.B Double\-click
Select word under cursor.
.TP
.B Drag
Select text.
.TP
.B Scroll wheel
Scroll viewport up/down.
.TP
.B Alt+Click
Add a multi\-cursor at the clicked position.
.TP
.B Click on tab bar
Switch to that buffer.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B Zedit
reads its configuration from
.IR ~/.config/zedit/config.json .
Example:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{
    "tab_size": 4,
    "use_spaces": true,
    "theme": "zedit\-dark",
    "line_numbers": true,
    "auto_indent": true,
    "word_wrap": false,
    "lsp": {
        "rust": { "command": "rust\-analyzer" },
        "python": { "command": "pylsp" }
    },
    "keybindings": {
        "toggle_minimap": "Alt+M"
    },
    "languages": [
        {
            "name": "ruby",
            "extensions": ["rb", "rake"],
            "grammar": "ruby.tmLanguage.json",
            "comment": "#"
        }
    ]
}
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B tab_size
Number of spaces per indentation level (1\(en16, default 4).
.TP
.B use_spaces
If true (default), Tab inserts spaces. If false, inserts a literal tab.
.TP
.B theme
Color theme name. Built\-in themes:
.BR zedit\-dark ", " zedit\-light .
Custom themes go in
.IR ~/.config/zedit/themes/ .
.TP
.B line_numbers
Show line number gutter (default true).
.TP
.B auto_indent
Preserve indentation on Enter (default true).
.TP
.B word_wrap
Wrap long lines visually (default false).
.TP
.B lsp
Object mapping language IDs to LSP server configurations. Each entry has a
.B command
field (executable name or path) and an optional
.B args
array. The language ID must match the
.B name
field of a language definition (e.g. "rust", "python", "typescript").
.TP
.B keybindings
Object mapping action names to key strings (e.g. "Ctrl+Shift+M").
Valid modifiers: Ctrl, Alt, Shift. Key names: single characters,
Enter, Tab, Backspace, Delete, Escape, Up, Down, Left, Right, Home, End,
PageUp, PageDown, F1\(enF12, Space, Backtick, Backslash, Slash.
.TP
.B languages
Array of language definitions. Each entry has:
.BR name " (language identifier),"
.BR extensions " (file extension list),"
.BR grammar " (TextMate grammar filename),"
.BR comment " (line comment prefix, optional)."
User entries override built\-in languages by name.
.SH LSP CONFIGURATION
Zedit starts language servers on demand when a file of a matching language is
opened. Servers must be installed separately (e.g.
.B rust\-analyzer
from the Rust toolchain,
.B pylsp
via pip). Configure them in
.IR ~/.config/zedit/config.json :
.PP
.RS
.nf
{
    "lsp": {
        "rust":       { "command": "rust\-analyzer" },
        "python":     { "command": "pylsp" },
        "typescript": { "command": "typescript\-language\-server",
                        "args": [\-\-stdio"] },
        "go":         { "command": "gopls" },
        "c":          { "command": "clangd" }
    }
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Diagnostics appear as colored underlines in the text and are counted in the
status bar (e.g. "E:2 W:1"). LSP completion, hover, and go\-to\-definition
require a running server.
.PP
.B Z ecosystem auto\-detection:
If
.B zenith\-lsp
or
.B zymbol\-lsp
are found on
.BR $PATH ,
zedit automatically registers them for the
.B zenith
and
.B zymbol
languages without any manual configuration.
.SH SYNTAX HIGHLIGHTING
.B Zedit
uses TextMate grammar files
.RB ( .tmLanguage.json )
for syntax highlighting. Built\-in grammars:
Rust, C, C++, Go, Java, JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, PHP, Julia, R,
JSON, TOML, YAML, Markdown, Shell/Bash, HTML, CSS, XML, Zenith, Zymbol, Minilux.
.PP
Grammar files are loaded from disk at runtime in the following search order:
.IP 1. 4
.IR ~/.config/zedit/grammars/ " (user\-provided, highest priority)"
.IP 2. 4
.IR /usr/share/zedit/grammars/ " and " /usr/local/share/zedit/grammars/ " (system\-wide)"
.IP 3. 4
.IR grammars/ " in the current working directory (development / source tree)"
.PP
Place any VS Code\-compatible
.I .tmLanguage.json
file in
.I ~/.config/zedit/grammars/
to add or override a grammar without recompiling. The grammar filename must
match the
.B grammar
field in the language definition.
.PP
Themes follow the VS Code color theme format. Color output adapts automatically
to the terminal's capabilities (24\-bit, 256\-color, or 16\-color).
.SH GIT GUTTER
When a file is inside a git repository, zedit shows change markers in the
left gutter next to the line numbers:
.TP
.B +
(green) \(em line added since HEAD
.TP
.B ~
(yellow) \(em line modified since HEAD
.TP
.B \-
(red) \(em lines deleted (shown on the adjacent line)
.PP
The gutter updates automatically as you edit.
.SH SESSION AND SWAP
Zedit saves the current session (open files, cursor positions, scroll offsets)
automatically on exit. Running
.B zedit
without arguments restores the previous session.
.PP
Swap files are written every 2 seconds while editing. If zedit crashes,
the next launch detects orphaned swap files and offers to recover them.
.SH PLUGINS
Plugins are external processes that communicate with zedit over newline\-delimited
JSON on stdin/stdout. Currently the Minilux runtime is supported.
.PP
Place each plugin in its own subdirectory of
.IR ~/.config/zedit/plugins/ ,
with a
.B manifest.json
describing it:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{
    "name": "myplugin",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "description": "Does something useful",
    "main": "main.mlx"
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Plugins can register palette commands, subscribe to editor events
.RB ( buffer_open ", " buffer_save ", " buffer_close ", " cursor_move ", " text_change ),
read and insert buffer text, and show status bar messages.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/zedit/config.json
Editor configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/zedit/grammars/
User\-provided TextMate grammar files (.tmLanguage.json).
.TP
.I ~/.config/zedit/themes/
User\-provided VS Code\-compatible color theme files.
.TP
.I ~/.config/zedit/extensions/
Native extension directories (managed by
.BR \-\-ext ).
.TP
.I ~/.config/zedit/plugins/
Plugin directories (one subdirectory per plugin).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/zedit/sessions/
Session persistence files (auto\-saved on exit).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/zedit/swap/
Swap files for crash recovery.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B COLORTERM
If set to
.BR truecolor " or " 24bit ,
enables 24\-bit true color output.
.TP
.B TERM
Used to detect 256\-color support (e.g.,
.BR xterm\-256color ).
Falls back to 16\-color mode otherwise.
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate
.I ~/.config/zedit/
and plugin directories.
